ely many times; the system responds solely with the count of correct answers. Please design an optimal algorithm to determine the correct answers for all questions and provide a complexity analysis.\n\nNotes:\n1. For each submission attempt, the questions and their sequence remain fixed.\n2. If the correct answers for all questions are logically deduced prior to submitting an all-correct submission, a final submission of the perfect answer sheet is not required.\n3. "Optimal" may define the minimization of either the expected number of attempts or the number of attempts in the worst-case scenario. Should these criteria diverge, you are required to design two distinct algorithms.'}], 'model': 'nex/nex-n1.1', 'max_tokens': 20000, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}, 'temperature': 0.3}}
